[2
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 1998 19:51:44 +0100
From: Martin Schweiger <GERMBUSTER@schwefam.demon.co.uk>

I am a Consultant in Communicable Disease Control in Leeds, Yorkshire,
England.
We have a serious problems with head lice in this area. Many health
professionals are involved in dealing with this problem and I get many
queries. Your niece's problem does not sound like a usual reaction to
head lice, but might be a drug reaction. Do you know how the head lice were
treated?
If you are interested the Leeds Health Authority Head lice Policy is
available on line from <http://www.schwefam.demon.co.uk/lice.htm>
NB Do not always blame school contacts ... lice require head to head contact
which is more common in social rather than school settings.
--
Martin Schweiger
e-mail: germbuster@schwefam.demon.co.uk
http://www.schwefam.demon.co.uk
