[6
Date: Mon, 20 Apr 1998 16:53:04 -0700
From: DeBolt, Chas <Chas.DeBolt@metrokc.gov>

In reading this description of reappearance of symptoms with re exposure to
the parasite, it seems that the individual may have some type of allergic
response to the interaction between her body and the lice. Perhaps she is
being bitten and is reacting to a saliva protein? I say this based on
personal experience with an allergy to dust mites which can range from
itching and skin wheels to asthma and pneumonia, depending on the "dose" and
the way in which I am exposed. Swollen lymph nodes and URI symptoms are one
of my responses.
--
